post_text:
The Soledad Education Foundation under the consultation of the Monterey County Health Department is cancelling this year’s SEF Carnival. This is the result of the international concerns with regard to the Coronavirus. The safety of our community, students, parents, and staff are of the utmost importance to us. We thank you for your understanding and continued support.

For those who have purchased tickets, we will provide more direction at a later time.

La Fundación de Educación de Soledad, bajo la consulta del Departamento de Salud del Condado de Monterey, cancelará este año el Carnaval de la Fundacion de Educacion de Soledad. Este es el resultado de las preocupaciones internacionales con respecto al Coronavirus. La seguridad de nuestra comunidad, estudiantes, padres y personal es de suma importancia para nosotros. Le agradecemos su comprensión y apoyo continuo.

Para aquellos que hayan comprado boletos, les proporcionaremos más instrucciones más adelante.

post_text: You may have received a text message that says "Soledad Unified School District alerts. Reply Y 2 confirm..." If you received this message, you are probably listed as a contact for a student enrolled with Soledad Unified, and it is only asking you to opt in if you would like to receive our alerts. This is not an emergency alert. It was sent by mistake. Sorry for the confusion.
